<title>UK: BSkyB drops on News Corp plans.</title>
<headline>BSkyB drops on News Corp plans.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-10-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>British Sky Broadcasting's shares fell in heavy trade on Thursday, hit by news that Rupert Murdoch's News Corp planned to mortgage part of its stake in the company via a convertible preference share issue.</p>
<p>&quot;It shows that Murdoch obviously thinks the (share) value is quite high at the moment to be doing it at this time,&quot; said Jason Crisp, analyst at SocGen. The satellite broadcaster's shares dropped 31p to 605p by 0850 GMT, after News Corp said it would sell $1 billion of preferred securities for the purchase of stock in BSkyB.</p>
